      • createNewBucket

        public BucketEntry createNewBucket(int bucketNumber,
                                   VaultEntry entry)
        This method creates a new BucketEntry out of the given int and VaultEntry. The int is the consecutive numbering of the BucketEntry. During the process the VaultEntryType will be checked and all necessary inputs for the arrays inside the BucketEntry will be generated accordingly.
        Parameters:
        bucketNumber - The consecutive number of the BucketEntry that is being created.
        entry - The VaultEntry that will be stored inside the BucketEntry.
        Returns:
        This method returns a newly created BucketEntry

      • createEmptyBucket

        public BucketEntry createEmptyBucket(int bucketNumber,
                                     java.util.Date date)
                              throws java.text.ParseException
        This method creates a new empty BucketEntry out of the given int and Date. The int is the consecutive numbering of the BucketEntry. A new VaultEntry will be created containing the VauleEntryType EMPTY and the given Date.
        Parameters:
        bucketNumber - The consecutive number of the BucketEntry that is being created.
        date - The Date (timestamp) that is needed to create a vaild VaultEntry
        Returns:

        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException

      • createListOfBuckets

        public java.util.List<BucketEntry> createListOfBuckets(java.util.List<VaultEntry> entryList)
                                                throws java.text.ParseException
        This method creates a list of BucketEntrys out of a list of VaultEntrys. This method checks if each VaultEntry is ML-relevant and if it is then a new BucketEntry with the given VaultEntry is created and if not then a new empty BucketEntry will be crated in it's place. This method also creates a BucketEntry for every minute that passes starting from the timestamp of the first given VaultEntry and ending with the timestamp of the last given VaultEntry. Do not call this method with null as an imput.
        Parameters:
        entryList - This is the list of VaultEntrys that will be converted into a list of BucketEntrys.
        Returns:
        This method returns the list of BucketEntrys that is generated out of the given list of VaultEntrys.
        Throws:
        java.text.ParseException

      • setBucketArrayInformation

        public void setBucketArrayInformation(java.util.Date date,
                                      BucketEntry bucket)
        This method sets the necessary information into the BucketEntry arrays and manages the onehot markers, onehot timers, and merge-tos. The Date expected is the timeCounter from createListOfBuckets. The BucketEntry that is given to this method will have it's arrays updated according to the input of the previous BucketEntrys that have been in this method. The first call of this method musst be done with the BucketEntry with the bucketEntryNumber 1.
        Parameters:
        date - This is the current Date from the method createListOfBuckets (timecounter).
        bucket - This is the BucketEntry that will have it's arrays updated.
